 And then we are going to assign that to save.

00:11:35.960 --> 00:11:40.960
 So that's the place we're going to save this new item.

00:11:40.960 --> 00:11:46.960
 The next thing we're going to do is allocate a brand new l node, a brand new node in our list.

00:11:46.960 --> 00:11:52.960
 And we're going to malloc size of struct l node and then we're going to cast it to a struct l node star.

00:11:52.960 --> 00:11:57.960
 And then we're going to assign that into a struct l node star variable named new.

00:11:57.960 --> 00:12:06.960
 We saved our string and we've got a pointer to that save string and a pointer to a empty at this point l node.

00:12:06.960 --> 00:12:22.960
 Then what we do is we connect with if tail is not equal to null, tail next equals new. So we take the about to be second to last item and we connect it to the last item.

