 And then what we do is we take the text pointer inside of our newly allocated list node and point it at the saved copy of our string in dynamic memory.

00:12:33.960 --> 00:12:43.960
 And then we point the next to be null and then we simply advance tail so that next time we do this tail is pointing to the new end of the string.

00:12:43.960 --> 00:12:50.960
 Now we've got one more thing that we've got to do and that is if head is null we have to set head to new.

